<card id="intro" title="WinWAP introduction">
<p align="center">
   <img src="..\images\wwbyst.wbmp" alt="WinWAP"/>
</p>
<p>
  <br/>
  WinWAP is a browser that reads wireless markup language (wml) formatted data.
  The browser looks, and functions much like any standard html browser, but instead
  of reading hypertext transfer markup language data ( html ) it is designed for wml.
  It supports 3 ways of getting the data.
  <br/>
  <br/>
  <big>1) HTTP</big>
  <br/>
  Hyper text transfer protocol is the same protocol that is used to read "normal"
  internet pages with a computer over a tcp/ip connection.
  <br/>
  <br/>
  <big>2) WAP Gateway</big><b> </b>
  <br/>
  The Gateway option enables the browser to connect directly to Wap gateways. This is the
  same way that cellular phones connect when using wap.
  <br/>
  <br/>

  <big>3) Local File</big>
  <br/>
  WinWAP can open .wml files locally from a drive on the computer ( or network drive ).
</p>
